Jidenna and Sarkodie have joined the host of artistes who will be performing at the One Africa Music Festival at the Wembley SSE Arena on May 13.They join the likes of Davido, Tekno, Tiwa Savage, P-Square, The Compozers, Olamide, Cassper Nyovest, Alikiba, Flavour N'abania, Phyno, M. I, 9ice, Efya, Awilo Longomba, Falz, and Victoria Kimani.This year's One Africa Music Festival comes after two successful shows were held at the Barclays Centre (New York) and the Toyota Centre (Houston) last year. Last year's edition featured Wizkid, D'banj, Jidenna, Flavour, Seun Kuti, Swizz Beatz, DJ Ebro, Lil Mama, Angela Simmonsand, and many other artistes.The festival will be hosted by Banky W, with Capital Xtra's Aberantee Boatengbeing the official UK DJ.